Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.52,0:10:09.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以及我們創作的音樂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the music we made.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.74,0:10:22.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}浩瀚宇宙海洋中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The deeper waters
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:24.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更深層的水流裏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of this vast cosmic ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.47,0:10:28.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也存在著數不盡的世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and their numberless worlds lie ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.89,0:10:44.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}從這裏看 太陽好像和其他星星並無兩樣\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}From out here, the Sun may look like just another star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:47.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但它的引力場依然影響著\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it still exerts its gravitational hold
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.23,0:10:49.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}數萬億的冰凍彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on a trillion frozen comets,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.63,0:10:52.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}還有太陽系中那些形成於大約50億年前的\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}leftovers from the formation of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.40,0:10:55.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其他所有組成部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}nearly five billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.23,0:10:57.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們稱之為 奧爾特雲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's called the Oort Cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.87,0:11:00.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以前從沒有人見過 也不可能見過\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No one has ever seen it before, nor could they,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.61,0:11:02.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因為這些天體\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because each one of these little worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.88,0:11:05.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}與它最近的鄰居之間的距離\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is as far from its nearest neighbor
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.11,0:11:08.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和地球與土星的距離差不多 (12-16億公里）\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}as Earth is from Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.75,0:11:12.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這個包含太陽系的巨大彗星雲團\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This enormous cloud of comets encloses the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.58,0:11:16.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是我們宇宙地址的第二行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is the second line of our cosmic address.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.39,0:11:20.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球\n太陽系
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.29,0:11:24.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們有能力探測其他星系的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've only been able to detect the planets of other stars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.96,0:11:26.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也就是最近幾十年的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a few decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.97,0:11:30.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我們已經知道行星的數量是很多的\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}but we already know that planets are plentiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.74,0:11:33.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比恒星的數量要多得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they outnumber the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.41,0:11:36.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}幾乎所有的行星都和地球很不一樣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Almost all of them will be very different from Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.84,0:11:39.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不適合生物生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and hostile to life as we know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.34,0:11:41.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我們對於生物又有多少瞭解呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what do we know about life?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.75,0:11:44.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}目前我們只接觸過一種\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've met only one kind so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.82,0:11:46.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earthlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.79,0:11:48.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到什麼了嗎？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}See anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.12,0:11:50.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是空蕩蕩的太空 對嗎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just empty space, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:54.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人類的眼睛只能看到宇宙中的一絲光亮\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}Human eyes see only a sliver of the light that shines in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.93,0:11:59.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是科技讓我們可以看到肉眼無法看到的\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}But science gives us the power to see what our senses cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.16,0:12:03.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}夜視鏡可以讓我們看見紅外線\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Infrared is the kind of light made visible by night-vision goggles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.97,0:12:06.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向黑暗中發射一個紅外感應器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Throw an infrared sensor across the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.04,0:12:09.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}流浪行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rogue planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.68,0:12:11.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不繞恒星公轉的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}World without a sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.85,0:12:18.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們的銀河中有數十億顆遊蕩在永恆的黑夜中\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}Our galaxy has billions of them, adrift in perpetual night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.32,0:12:21.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在他們原本的星系誕生時的混亂中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're orphans, cast away from their mother stars
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.89,0:12:25.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他們像孤兒一樣失去了恒星母親\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}during the chaotic birth of their native star systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.06,0:12:29.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}流浪行星有著熔岩般的內核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rogue planets are molten at the core
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.73,0:12:31.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但表面卻被嚴寒覆蓋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but frozen at the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.73,0:12:33.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在這些極端區域的中間\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There may be oceans of liquid water
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.73,0:12:36.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也許存在著大洋般的液態水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the zone between those extremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.31,0:12:44.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}誰又能知道水中生活著什麼東西呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Who knows what might be swimming there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.68,0:12:52.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這是銀河的紅外線顯示圖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is what the Milky Way looks like in infrared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.89,0:12:55.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每個小點 不僅僅是那些明亮的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every single dot, not just the bright ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.99,0:12:58.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都是一顆恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.19,0:13:00.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這裏有多少顆恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How many stars?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.19,0:13:02.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有多少不同的世界呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How many worlds?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.19,0:13:04.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}又有多少不同的生命存在的方式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How many ways of being alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:07.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們又身處圖片中的何處呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where are we in this picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.70,0:13:10.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到那條螺旋臂了嗎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}See that trailing outer arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:19.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太陽系\n銀河系
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.17,0:13:12.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們就在那裏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's where we live...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.37,0:13:15.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}距離中心3萬光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 30,000 light-years from the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.61,0:13:17.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}銀河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Milky Way Galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.34,0:13:20.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們宇宙地址的下一行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the next line of our cosmic address.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.68,0:13:23.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們現在離家十萬光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're now a hundred thousand light-years from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.08,0:13:26.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光波 存在的速度最快的東西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would take light, the fastest thing there is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.35,0:13:30.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要花10萬年才能從地球到達我們這裏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a hundred thousand years to reach us from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.96,0:13:35.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這是僊女座螺旋星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the Great Spiral in Andromeda,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.39,0:13:37.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}銀河系的隔壁鄰居\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the galaxy next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.40,0:13:39.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們將這兩大星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We call our two giant galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.40,0:13:41.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和一些較小的星系稱為\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a smattering of smaller ones
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.40,0:13:43.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}本星系群\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the "local group."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.83,0:13:56.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太陽系\n銀河系\n本星系群
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.12,0:13:59.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太陽系\n銀河系\n本星系群\n室女座超星系團
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.41,0:13:54.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}從這裏已經看不到銀河系了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Can't even find our home galaxy from out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.75,0:13:58.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它只是室女座超星系團中的幾千份之一\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}It's just one of thousands in the Virgo Supercluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.98,0:14:00.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以這個比例來說\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On this scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.92,0:14:04.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們所看到的 哪怕是最小的點\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the objects we see, including the tiniest dots,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.56,0:14:06.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都是一個星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.39,0:14:08.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每個星系包含幾十億顆恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each galaxy contains billions of suns
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.96,0:14:11.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和數不清的行星世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and countless worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.06,0:14:14.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然而 整個室女座超星系團\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yet, the entire Virgo Supercluster itself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.73,0:14:17.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是我們宇宙的一個極小組成部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}forms but a tiny part of our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.64,0:14:23.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這是我們已知的最大範圍的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the cosmos on the grandest scale we know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.64,0:14:26.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一張由數以千億的星系組成的大網\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a network of a hundred billion galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.98,0:14:30.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也是我們宇宙地址的最後一行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the last line of our cosmic address...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.45,0:14:32.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}截止目前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.98,0:14:32.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}地球\n太陽系\n銀河系\n本星系群 室女座超星系團\n可觀測宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.02,0:14:35.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可觀測宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Observable universe?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.52,0:14:37.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}什麼意思\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.42,0:14:40.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即使我們在想像之舟中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even for us, in our Ship of the Imagination,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.19,0:14:43.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在時空中所能看到的也是有限的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there's a limit to how far we can see in space-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.83,0:14:46.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這是我們的宇宙水平線\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's our cosmic horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.27,0:14:49.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一部分的宇宙處於水平線之下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Beyond that horizon lie parts of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.37,0:14:51.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}離我們實在太遙遠了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.54,0:14:53.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在僅有的時間裏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There hasn't been enough time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.54,0:14:56.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在宇宙138億年的歷史中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the 13.8 billion year history of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.64,0:14:59.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光線還來不及傳遞過來\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for their light to have reached us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.18,0:15:04.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很多人猜測 所有的這一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many of us suspect that all of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.62,0:15:08.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有的行星 恒星 星系 星團\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the worlds, stars, galaxies and clusters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.85,0:15:11.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們的可觀測宇宙中的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in our observable universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.29,0:15:18.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是其他宇宙中的滄海一粟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is but one tiny bubble in an infinite ocean of other universes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.67,0:15:22.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}多重宇宙論\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...a multiverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:25.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙之上的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Universe upon universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.97,0:15:28.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}沒有盡頭的世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Worlds without end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.25,0:15:35.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}感覺很渺小嗎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Feeling a little small?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.35,0:15:38.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相對宇宙來說 我們確實很渺小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, in the contexts of the cosmos, we are small.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.85,0:15:42.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們或許只是生活在這浩瀚宇宙中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We may just be little guys living on a speck of dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.19,0:15:44.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}漂浮的灰塵粒上的小不點\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}afloat in a staggering immensity,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.59,0:15:46.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但我們並不坐井觀天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we don't think small.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.73,0:15:50.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}現在的宇宙論誕生並不久遠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This cosmic perspective is relatively new.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.20,0:15:54.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}僅僅400年前 我們尚未認識\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A mere four centuries ago, our tiny world was oblivious
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.50,0:15:56.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}自身世界以外的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the rest of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.50,0:15:58.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那時沒有望遠鏡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There were no telescopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.50,0:16:02.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只能看到我們肉眼可見的部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe was only what you could see with the naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.27,0:16:04.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在1599年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Back in 1599,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.38,0:16:07.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有人都認為太陽 行球 星星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}everyone knew that the Sun, planets and stars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.75,0:16:11.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是環繞地球的亮光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were just lights in the sky that revolved around the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.78,0:16:15.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而我們是宇宙的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that we were the center of a little universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.85,0:16:18.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由上帝為我們創造的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a universe made for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.19,0:16:22.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}當時全世界只有一個人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There was only one man on the whole planet
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.60,0:16:25.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想像著一個無盡的浩瀚宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who envisioned an infinitely grander cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.46,0:16:31.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他是怎麼度過他的1600年除夕？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And how was he spending New Year's Eve of the year 1600?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.20,0:16:34.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}當然是在監獄裏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why, in prison, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.16,0:16:44.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命中總有那麼一天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There comes a time in our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.36,0:16:47.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們發現自己並不是宇宙的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when we first realize we're not the center of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.63,0:16:50.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們以外還有更廣大的世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we belong to something much greater than ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.87,0:16:52.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這是我們成長所需經歷的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's part of growing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.87,0:16:55.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因為每個人都會經歷到這段過程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And as it happens to each of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.14,0:16:57.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們的文明也在16世紀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it began to happen to our civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.48,0:16:59.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也經歷著這樣的成長\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the 16th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.18,0:17:02.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想像一下望遠鏡問世之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine a world before telescopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.08,0:17:05.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們只能靠肉眼觀察這個宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the universe was only what you could see with the naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.88,0:17:09.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很顯然地球是靜止不動的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was obvious that Earth was motionless,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.09,0:17:10.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天空中的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that everything in the heavens...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.82,0:17:13.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太陽 月亮 星星 星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Sun, the Moon, the stars, the planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.16,0:17:15.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都圍繞著我們運行  然後\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}revolved around us... and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.03,0:17:18.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一位名叫哥白尼的波蘭天文學家兼牧師\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}a Polish astronomer and priest named Copernicus
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.33,0:17:22.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}提出一個地球並非中心的激進假想\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}made a radical proposal. The Earth was not the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.33,0:17:26.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球只是和其他星星一樣的行星繞著太陽旋轉\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}It was just one of the planets, and, like them, it revolved around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.84,0:17:30.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很多人 例如宗教改革發起人馬丁·路德\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}Many, like the Protestant reformer Martin Luther,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.17,0:17:33.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}認為這是在對聖經的可恥侮辱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}took this idea as a scandalous affront to Scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.18,0:17:35.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他們震怒了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They were horrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.45,0:17:39.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是另一個人卻認為哥白尼說的不全面\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}But for one man, Copernicus didn't go far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.92,0:17:43.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他叫焦爾達諾·布魯諾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His name was Giordano Bruno and he was a natural-born rebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.31,0:17:44.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他生性反叛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and he was a natural-born rebel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:47.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他渴望打破這狹隘宇宙的枷鎖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He longed to bust out of that cramped little universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.68,0:17:50.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在那不勒斯做道明會的修道士時\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even as a young Dominican monk in Naples,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.48,0:17:51.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他就與這個世界格格不入\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he was a misfit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.94,0:17:54.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}當時在義大利沒有思想的自由\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was a time when there was no freedom of thought in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.69,0:17:56.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是布魯諾渴望瞭解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Bruno hungered to know
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.12,0:17:57.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}關於上帝創世的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}everything about God's creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.96,0:18:00.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他閱讀了被教廷禁止的書籍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He dared to read the books banned by the Church,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.37,0:18:03.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}從此踏上了不歸路\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that was his undoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.49,0:18:05.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這些書籍中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In one of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.20,0:18:09.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有一本的作者是1500年前的古羅馬人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an ancient Roman, a man dead for more than 1,500 years
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.20,0:18:09.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}物性論 - 盧克·萊修
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.34,0:18:12.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向他描述了一個更廣闊的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whispered to him of a universe far greater,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.31,0:18:15.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}廣闊的猶如他的上帝一般\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one as boundless as his idea of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.45,0:18:21.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}盧克萊修讓他的讀者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Lucretius asked the reader
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:23.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想像站在宇宙的邊緣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to imagine standing at the edge of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.86,0:18:25.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向外射出一支箭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and shooting an arrow outward.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.86,0:18:28.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果箭繼續前進 那麼很明顯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If the arrow keeps going, then clearly,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.16,0:18:31.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙繼續向所謂的邊緣以外延伸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the universe extends beyond what you thought was the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.06,0:18:33.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是如果箭不繼續前進\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if the arrow doesn't keep going...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.50,0:18:36.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比方說 撞在一堵牆上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}say it hits a wall... then that wall must lie
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.20,0:18:39.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那麼牆必然是處在所謂的邊緣之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}beyond what you thought was the edge of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.17,0:18:42.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那麼如果你站在這堵牆上向外射箭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now if you stand on that wall and shoot another arrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.51,0:18:45.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也只有這相同的兩個結果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there are only the same two possible outcomes...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.24,0:18:47.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要麼是飛入無盡的太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it either flies forever out into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.65,0:18:49.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要麼是撞在某個障礙物上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or it hits some boundary
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:52.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然後你又可以站在上面射出另一支箭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where you can stand and shoot yet another arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.42,0:18:54.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}無論如何 宇宙是沒有界限的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Either way, the universe is unbounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:58.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙必然是無盡的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cosmos must be infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.32,0:19:00.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布魯諾深以為然\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This made perfect sense to Bruno.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.83,0:19:03.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他崇拜的上帝是全能的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The God he worshiped was infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.19,0:19:07.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以他斷定 上帝創造的宇宙怎會不是無窮\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}So how, he reasoned, could Creation be anything less?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.74,0:19:24.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是他的最後一份穩定工作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was the last steady job he ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.13,0:19:37.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}後來 當他30歲時\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then, when he was 30,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.56,0:19:41.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的一個幻覺從此改變他的一生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he had the vision that sealed his fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.23,0:19:43.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在這個夢中 他認識到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In this dream, he awakened to a world
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.73,0:19:46.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一個包含在一群行星中的世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}enclosed inside a confining bowl of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.80,0:19:49.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是他那個時代的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was the cosmos of Bruno's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.26,0:20:10.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他感到一陣不舒服的害怕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He experienced a sickening moment of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.83,0:20:12.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像腳下的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as if the bottom of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.36,0:20:14.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}正向下墜落\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was falling away beneath his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.00,0:20:17.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是他鼓起了勇氣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But he summoned up his courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.51,0:20:28.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我展開自信的翅膀飛向太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I spread confident wings to space
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.35,0:20:31.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向上高飛至無盡的天空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and soared toward the infinite, leaving far behind me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.95,0:20:35.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}將一切的壓力拋在身後\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what others strained to see from a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.32,0:20:38.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這裏沒有上 沒有下 沒有邊界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here, there was no up, no down, no edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.72,0:20:40.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}沒有中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no center.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.29,0:20:43.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我看見太陽和其他星星一樣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I saw that the Sun was just another star,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.73,0:20:47.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}還有其他被行星伴隨著的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the stars were other Suns, each escorted by other Earths
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.70,0:20:49.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像我們的太陽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.33,0:20:54.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這巨大的啟示對他就如同墜入愛河\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The revelation of this immensity was like falling in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.54,0:20:59.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布魯諾變成了一個傳教士\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bruno became an evangelist,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.54,0:21:02.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他在歐洲各地宣揚他的宇宙無限論\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spreading the gospel of infinity throughout Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.98,0:21:06.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他以為其他上帝的追隨者會同樣接受\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He assumed that other lovers of God would naturally embrace
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.58,0:21:09.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這個對於創世的偉大且榮耀的觀點\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this grander and more glorious view of Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.65,0:21:12.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我是不是太傻了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What a fool I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.73,0:21:18.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在他的祖國 他被羅馬天主教會開除教籍\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}He was excommunicated by the Roman Catholic Church in his homeland,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.36,0:21:20.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他不僅被瑞士加爾文長老會驅逐出境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}expelled by the Calvinists in Switzerland,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.83,0:21:23.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}還被德國的路德教派驅逐出境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and by the Lutherans in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.07,0:21:28.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布魯諾接受了一份邀請到英國牛津大學講課\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}Bruno jumped at an invitation to lecture at Oxford, in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.34,0:21:32.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他認為這是一個機會\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At last, he thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.21,0:21:35.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以與他類似的人分享他的觀點\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a chance to share his vision with an audience of his peers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.95,0:21:43.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我來介紹一個對於宇宙的嶄新看法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I have come to present a new vision of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.05,0:21:46.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哥白尼是對的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Copernicus was right to argue that our world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.12,0:21:47.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們的世界並不是宇宙的中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is not the center of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.86,0:21:49.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球繞著太陽旋轉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth goes around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.93,0:21:52.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它和其他行星一樣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a planet, just like the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.43,0:21:54.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但哥白尼只是曙光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Copernicus was only the dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.53,0:21:56.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而我為你們帶來日出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I bring you the sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.10,0:22:00.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那些星星和我們炙熱的太陽一樣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars are other fiery suns,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.20,0:22:02.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由和地球一樣的天體組成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}made of the same substance as the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.44,0:22:05.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他們也有自己的含水的地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they have their own watery earths,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.48,0:22:08.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上面有著和我們一樣高貴的動物植物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with plants and animals no less noble than our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.58,0:22:10.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你是瘋了還是太蠢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Are you mad or merely ignorant?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.88,0:22:12.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}眾所周知只有一個世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everyone knows there is only one world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.65,0:22:15.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是錯誤的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What everyone knows is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.15,0:22:18.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們全能的上帝創造了一個無邊無際的宇宙\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}Our infinite God has created a boundless universe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.16,0:22:20.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其中包含了無數的星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with an infinite number of worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.06,0:22:22.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你們那的人沒讀過亞里斯多德的書嗎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Do they not read Aristotle where you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.09,0:22:23.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或者是聖經嗎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or even the Bible?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.83,0:22:28.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我請求你摒棄老舊和傳統的信仰和權威\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}I beg you, reject antiquity, tradition, faith, and authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.47,0:22:29.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}讓我們重新認識\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let us begin anew,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.77,0:22:31.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}質疑我們以為\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by doubting everything we assume
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.80,0:22:32.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}-已經被證實的一切 -異端者!\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}- has been proven. - Heretic!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.94,0:22:33.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}異教徒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Infidel!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.01,0:22:35.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你們信仰的上帝太小了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Your God is too small.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.45,0:22:43.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}明智的人本應該從中吸取了教訓\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A wiser man would have learned his lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.85,0:22:47.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可惜布魯諾並不是那個人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Bruno was not such a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.19,0:22:51.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他不停的宣揚自己觀點\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He couldn't keep his soaring vision of the cosmos to himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.46,0:22:54.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}儘管這會帶來沉痛的代價\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}despite the fact that the penalty for doing so
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.43,0:22:57.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在他的那個時代 代價是如此的殘酷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in his world was the most vicious form
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.46,0:22:59.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}無情和更嚴厲的懲罰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of cruel and unusual punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.07,0:23:07.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}焦爾達諾·布魯諾生活的那個時代\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Giordano Bruno lived at a time when there was no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.77,0:23:09.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}沒有政教分離\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the separation of church and state,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.74,0:23:14.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}沒有言論自由神聖不可侵犯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or the notion that freedom of speech was a sacred right of every individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.28,0:23:17.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}表達與傳統信仰相悖的觀點\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Expressing an idea that didn't conform to traditional belief
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.15,0:23:19.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}會帶來極大的麻煩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could land you in deep trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.75,0:23:24.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布魯諾不顧一切地回到了義大利\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Recklessly, Bruno returned to Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.45,0:23:26.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也許是想家了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe he was homesick.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.12,0:23:29.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可是他必須知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But still, he must have known that his homeland
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.39,0:23:31.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的祖國對他來說\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was one of the most dangerous places in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.49,0:23:33.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是最危險的國家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he could possibly go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:36.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由羅馬天主教會管轄的宗教法庭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Roman Catholic Church maintained a system of courts
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.33,0:23:38.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被稱為異端裁判所\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}known as the Inquisition,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.17,0:23:41.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它唯一職責就是審查和折磨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its sole purpose was to investigate and torment
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.74,0:23:45.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}與教會持有不同聲音和觀點的人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}anyone who dared voice views that differed from theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.65,0:23:52.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布魯諾很快就被\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It wasn't long before Bruno fell into the clutches
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.62,0:23:54.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}思想員警抓獲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the thought police.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.52,0:24:03.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這位信奉無限宇宙的流浪者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This wanderer, who worshiped an infinite universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.19,0:24:06.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在八年的監獄生涯中飽受煎熬\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}languished in confinement for eight years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.36,0:24:08.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}儘管受盡殘酷的審訊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Through relentless interrogations,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.20,0:24:10.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他依然不願放棄他的觀點\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he stubbornly refused to renounce his views.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.93,0:24:12.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}為什麼教會要花\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why was the Church willing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.50,0:24:16.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如此長的時間來折磨布魯諾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to go to such lengths to torment Bruno?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.21,0:24:18.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他們在害怕什麼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What were they afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.62,0:24:21.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果布魯諾是對的 那麼這些聖典\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If Bruno was right, then the sacred books
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.86,0:24:24.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}還有教會的權威\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the authority of the Church
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.71,0:24:28.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都將會受到質疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would be open to question.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.92,0:24:28.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最終 異端裁判所的紅衣主教們\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Finally, the cardinals of the Inquisition
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.66,0:24:30.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}做出了他們的判決\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rendered their verdict.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.59,0:24:32.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你有罪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You are found guilty
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.19,0:24:35.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你質疑聖父聖子聖靈三位一體\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of questioning the Holy Trinity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.06,0:24:37.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你質疑耶穌基督的神威\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the divinity of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.76,0:24:41.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你相信上帝的怒火不會永遠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of believing that God's wrath is not eternal,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.07,0:24:42.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有人都會被寬恕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that everyone will be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.57,0:24:47.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你斷言其他世界存在的主張\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of asserting the existence of other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.51,0:24:51.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你寫的所有書\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of the books you have written
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.44,0:24:54.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都會在聖彼得廣場前焚毀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will be gathered up and burned in St. Peter's Square.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.95,0:24:58.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尊敬的大人 8年的監禁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Reverend Father, these eight years of confinement
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.55,0:25:00.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}給了我很多時間去反省\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have given me much time to reflect.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.12,0:25:01.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然後呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.12,0:25:02.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你要放棄你的主張嗎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you will recant?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.52,0:25:04.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我對造物主的愛和崇敬\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}My love and reverence for the Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.52,0:25:08.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}激發我對全能的上帝的認識\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}inspires in me the vision of an infinite Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.20,0:25:11.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你拒不懺悔的話\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You shall be turned over to the Governor of Rome
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.80,0:25:15.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你會被移交到羅馬總督\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to administer the appropriate punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.20,0:25:17.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}予以執行相應的懲罰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for those who will not repent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.37,0:25:23.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可能你宣佈這個判決時的恐懼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It may be that you are more afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.31,0:25:26.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比我聽到判決的時候更厲害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to deliver this judgment than I am to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.78,0:26:37.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布魯諾殉難的10年後\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ten years after Bruno's martyrdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.05,0:26:39.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}伽利略通過望遠鏡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Galileo first looked through a telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.52,0:26:42.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}發現布魯諾的學說確實沒錯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}realizing that Bruno had been right all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.19,0:26:46.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}銀河系是由肉眼看不到的無數恒星組成\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}The Milky Way was made of countless stars invisible to the naked eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.69,0:26:50.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天空中的某些光亮其實是其他的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and some of those lights in the sky were actually other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.66,0:26:52.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布魯諾不是科學家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bruno was no scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.97,0:26:55.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他只是僥倖猜中了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His vision of the cosmos was a lucky guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.47,0:26:57.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因為沒有證據支持他\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because he had no evidence to support it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.97,0:27:01.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就和其他猜想一樣 也有可能不對\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like most guesses, it could well have turned out wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.24,0:27:03.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是這個觀點一旦散播出去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But once the idea was in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.84,0:27:05.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就給了其他人一個方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it gave others a target to aim at.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.91,0:27:07.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哪怕只是為了反駁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If only to disprove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.55,0:27:13.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布魯諾大致理解了太空的浩瀚無垠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bruno glimpsed the vastness of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.25,0:27:18.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但他對於時間的驚人無際沒有絲毫概念\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}But he had no inkling of the staggering immensity of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.60,0:27:24.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}壽命很少超過一個世紀的普通人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How can we humans, who rarely live more than a century,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.70,0:27:27.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}怎麼可能去理解宇宙的歷史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hope to grasp the vast expanse of time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.50,0:27:29.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像浩瀚寬闊的時間長河\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is the history of the cosmos?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.74,0:27:34.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙誕生於138億年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe is 13.8 thousand million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.54,0:27:36.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}為了更好地想像宇宙的歷史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In order to imagine all of cosmic time,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.94,0:27:40.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們把它壓縮成12個月的年曆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}let's compress it into a single calendar year.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.71,0:27:58.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}年曆上的1月1號是宇宙誕生的日子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cosmic calendar begins on January 1st with the birth of our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.73,0:28:01.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}年曆上包含了從那以後經歷的所有時間\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}It contains everything that's happened since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.42,0:28:02.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一直到現在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}up to now,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.80,0:28:07.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在這個年曆上的12月31號午夜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which on this calendar is midnight December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.35,0:28:11.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}按照這個比例 每個月代表10億年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On this scale, every month represents about a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.32,0:28:15.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每天代表將就4千萬年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every day represents nearly 40 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.88,0:28:17.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}讓我們盡可能地回到過去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let's go back as far as we can,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.77,0:28:20.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}回到宇宙最開始的時刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the very first moment of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.86,0:28:25.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1月1號 宇宙大爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}January 1st, the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.59,0:28:42.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}目前而言這是我們所能看到最早的時間\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}It's as far back as we can see in time... for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.22,0:28:47.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}整個宇宙形成於一個比原子還小的點\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our entire universe emerged from a point smaller than a single atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.05,0:28:51.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}空間在密度極大溫度極高的狀態下爆炸\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}Space itself exploded in a cosmic fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.05,0:28:53.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由此開始了宇宙的擴張\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}launching the expansion of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.42,0:28:55.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}並誕生了所有的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and giving birth to all the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.82,0:28:57.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}還有已經產生的那些所有我們已知的事物\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}and all the matter we know today.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.79,0:29:00.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}聽上去很瘋狂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I know that sounds crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.12,0:29:02.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我們有很強力的觀測證據\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but there's strong observational evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.09,0:29:03.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}來支持宇宙大爆炸理論\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to support the Big Bang theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.73,0:29:06.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}證據還有氦元素在宇宙中的比例\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it includes the amount of helium in the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.23,0:29:09.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以及爆炸殘留的發光無線電頻譜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the glow of radio waves left over from the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.90,0:29:12.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爆炸後宇宙開始冷卻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As it expanded, the universe cooled,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.40,0:29:17.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其間有2億年左右的黑暗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and there was darkness for about 200 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.31,0:29:20.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}萬有引力將氣體集聚並且加熱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity was pulling together clumps of gas and heating them
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.80,0:29:23.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到第一批恒星發出亮光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until the first stars burst into light
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.80,0:29:26.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相當於1月10號\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on January 10th.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.94,0:29:34.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1月13號 這些恒星開始結合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On January 13th, these stars coalesced
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.78,0:29:39.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}形成第一批小星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the first small galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.68,0:29:42.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}這些星系融合成更大的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These galaxies merged to form still larger ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.52,0:29:45.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包括我們的銀河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including our own Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.89,0:29:50.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}產生於110億年左右\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which formed about 11 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.36,0:29:53.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是宇宙年曆上的3月15號\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on March 15th of the cosmic year.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.07,0:29:57.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}數千億的恒星中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hundreds of billions of suns.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.57,0:29:59.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哪個是我們的太陽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Which one is ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.40,0:30:01.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}此時尚未誕生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not yet born.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.64,0:30:06.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它將從其他恒星的灰燼中產生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will rise from the ashes of other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.14,0:30:09.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到這些猶如閃光燈般的亮光嗎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}See those lights flashing like paparazzi?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.38,0:30:11.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它們都是超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each one is a supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.85,0:30:14.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一顆超大恒星的耀眼爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the blazing death of a giant star.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.02,0:30:18.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星消亡和誕生的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars die and are born in places like this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.42,0:30:20.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們稱為星星苗圃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a stellar nursery.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.42,0:30:20.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI}又稱分子雲
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.32,0:30:21.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他們像雨滴般\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They condense like raindrops
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.03,0:30:24.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}從巨大的氣態和灰塵雲中凝結\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from giant clouds of gas and dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.70,0:30:27.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他們溫度高的可以把原子中的原子核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They get so hot that the nuclei of the atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.70,0:30:30.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}融合在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}fuse together deep within them
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.23,0:30:33.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}從而產生了我們呼吸的氧氣 肌肉中的碳元素\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}to make the oxygen we breathe, the carbon in our muscles,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.44,0:30:36.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}骨頭中的鈣元素 血中的鐵元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the calcium in our bones, the iron in our blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.91,0:30:38.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有的這一切都產生於\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all of it was cooked
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.71,0:30:42.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}從此消亡的恒星炙熱的內心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the fiery hearts of long-vanished stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.21,0:30:45.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你 我 所有人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You, me, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.95,0:30:50.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們都是由星辰物質組成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we are made of star stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.19,0:30:54.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星辰物質被不斷迴圈和濃縮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This star stuff is recycled and enriched,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.52,0:30:56.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一遍又一遍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}again and again,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.09,0:30:58.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}經過幾代恒星的誕生消亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through succeeding generations of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.03,0:31:05.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}離我們的太陽誕生還有多久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How much longer until the birth of our Sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.44,0:31:07.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很長時間\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.24,0:31:08.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們太陽的第一次發光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It won't begin to shine
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.54,0:31:11.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}還要再等60億年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for another six billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.08,0:31:16.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太陽的生日是8月31號\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun's birthday is August 31st
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.08,0:31:17.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在這個宇宙年曆上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the Cosmic Calendar...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.42,0:31:22.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}45億年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...four and a half billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.72,0:31:25.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像太陽系中其他行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As with the other worlds of our solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.22,0:31:28.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球在一堆氣體和灰塵中產生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth was formed from a disk of gas and dust
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.33,0:31:30.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}繞著新生的太陽運行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}orbiting the newborn Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.49,0:31:33.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}反復的碰撞產生了一個發光的球狀碎片\N{\fs14\fn微軟雅黑}Repeated collisions produced a growing ball of debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.34,0:31:41.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到那個小行星了嗎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}See that asteroid?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.77,0:31:43.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不是那個\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No, not that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.11,0:31:44.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那邊的那個\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The one over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.81,0:31:48.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我們的存在歸功於它旁邊的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We exist because the gravity of that one next to it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.58,0:31:51.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把它輕輕向左推了一英吋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just nudged it an inch to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.75,0:31:53.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一英吋有很大的區別嗎\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What difference could an inch make
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.78,0:31:55.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}按照太陽系的比例來說\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the scale the solar system?
